China-Kazakhstan Snow festival | euronews, no comment
The first China-Kazakhstan snow cultural tourism festival opened on Thursday in the border city of Khorgos in China’s Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region.
The snow cultural tourism festival displayed 71 ice and snow sculptures shaped like dragons, camels, trains and the 12 Chinese zodiac signs for local residents and foreign visitors.
